{"type":"message","id":"fd45269b","parentId":"184f37f0","timestamp":"2026-04-10T10:20:58.027Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-0af76899f5f3441f9bd794338d7cbd4d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics Рђћ the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room Рєњ Main area, 180┬░ wide angle\n- front-door Рєњ Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server Рєњ 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775816458015}}
